'''Josué Duverger''' (born 27 April 2000) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Rheinlandliga]] club [[FC Cosmos Koblenz|Cosmos Koblenz]]. Born in Canada, he plays for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

== Club career ==
Josué Duverger began his club career in [[Portugal]]. Between 2015 and 2021, he appeared for the youth teams of [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]], [[Sporting CP Youth Academy|Sporting CP]], and [[Vitória F.C.|Vitória Setúbal]].

He made his first team debut for Vitória Setúbal in 2021 and transferred to [[União de Santarém|União Santarém]] in 2022. He then joined [[FC Cosmos Koblenz|Cosmos Koblenz]] in [[Rheinlandliga|the sixth tier of Germany]] in 2024.

==International career==
Born in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada, Duverguer is of Haitian descent. He was called up for an evaluation for the [[Canada men's national under-17 soccer team]] in October 2016.<ref name=CS>{{Canada Soccer player|4251|accessdate=15 September 2020}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Haiti national under-20 football team]] for the [[2017 CONCACAF U-20 Championship]] at the age of sixteen, appearing for all three of the teams' appearances in the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/category/under-20s-men/game-detail/381027|title=Under 20s – Men|website=CONCACAF|access-date=11 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227210858/http://www.concacaf.com/category/under-20s-men/game-detail/381027|archive-date=27 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/category/under-20s-men/game-detail/381016|title=Under 20s – Men|website=CONCACAF|access-date=11 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201211237/http://www.concacaf.com/category/under-20s-men/game-detail/381016|archive-date=1 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/category/under-20s-men/game-detail/381023|title=Under 20s – Men|website=CONCACAF|access-date=11 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111152229/http://www.concacaf.com/category/under-20s-men/game-detail/381023|archive-date=11 November 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was also called up to the [[Haiti national under-17 football team]] for the [[2017 CONCACAF U-17 Championship]], but didn't make any appearances for the team in the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/article/final-20-player-rosters-announced-for-the-concacaf-under-17-championship-panama-2017|title=Final 20-Player Rosters Announced for the CONCACAF Under-17 Championship Panama 2017|website=CONCACAF|access-date=11 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111204653/http://www.concacaf.com/article/final-20-player-rosters-announced-for-the-concacaf-under-17-championship-panama-2017|archive-date=11 November 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Duverguer made his debut for the senior [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] in a 1–0 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] win over the [[United Arab Emirates national football team|United Arab Emirates]] on 10 November 2017, at the age of seventeen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lenouvelliste.com/article/178833/haiti-fait-plier-les-emirats-arabes-unis|title=Haïti fait plier les Émirats arabes unis|publisher=}}</ref>

On 15 June 2021 in a match against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]], during [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONCACAF)|CONCACAF World Cup qualifying]], he mis-controlled a back pass and made two mis-kick attempts at a clearance as the ball rolled into the net for an [[Own goal#Association football|own goal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/.amp/extra-mustard/2021/06/16/haiti-canada-josue-duverger-own-goal-video|title=Haiti's Josué Duverger Surrendered an Unfathomably Terrible Own Goal vs. Canada &#124; Sports Illustrated|website=si.com}}</ref> The clip of the own goal went [[viral video|viral]] with some calling it one of the worst own goals ever seen.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/sport/football/haiti-goalkeeper-has-gone-viral-for-arguably-the-worst-own-goal-ever-scored-vs-canada/ar-AAL60Ot|title=Haiti goalkeeper has gone viral for arguably the worst own goal ever scored vs Canada|website=msn.com}}</ref>

